    <text id="A2923T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>In this letter, J. A. Spencer informs Henry Ott of the prices for Dry goods
                    locally, mentioning several local companies in the process.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Henry Ott, Esq.</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1866-09-17">Sept 17<hi rend="super">th</hi> 1866</date>
                        <name type="place">Midway</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Saml O. arrived yesterday He <orig reg="bought">Bot</orig> Shoes from B Pallerson
                    &amp; Bosk, No. 6 Bellween Charles &amp; Hanover. he refers us to that
                    house as the best in Bath. Davis waited on him, he also <orig reg="promised"
                        >promise</orig> Daniel Miller &amp; co to get us to Examine <orig
                        reg="their">there</orig> stock. Someone waited on him He is alone with
                        <unclear>Destries</unclear> &amp; co The Piece of goods I wrote you
                    about his Buying at 1.30 he <orig reg="bought">Bot</orig> from Bevan &amp;
                    Co. He <orig reg="bought">Bot</orig> good coffee for 25 cents From what he told
                    me I think he has <orig reg="bought">Bot</orig> a good lot of Dry goods. He is
                    goods will come to hand tomorrow. I write this by request of Nelson as he <orig
                        reg="promised">promise</orig> those parties to get us to call on them. If
                    you can have the Dry goods in Staunton friday write us by <orig reg="Thursday's"
                        >Thursdays</orig> Mail</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours &amp;c.</salute>
                    <signed>J. A. Spencer</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
